名词读作 ˈɪnsɛns ，动词读作 ɪnˈsɛns 。 

1. N-UNCOUNT Incense is a substance that is burned for its sweet smell, often as part of a religious ceremony. (常指祭祀时用的) 香 

2. V-T If you say that something incenses you, you mean that it makes you extremely angry. 使大怒 

例： This proposal will incense conservation campaigners. 这项提议将激怒自然保护的倡导者。 

